css.explanation:
css is a cascading style sheet which helps in styling html and xml files on browser.

Example:
```
.p {
   color: yellow;
   font-size: 34px;
}
```

```
[data-theme="dark"] form {
  background-color: #2a2a2a;
  color: #f1f1f1;
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
}

[data-theme="dark"] .form-group input,
[data-theme="dark"] .form-group textarea {
  background-color: #333;
  color: #fff;
  border-color: #555;
}

[data-theme="dark"] .form-group input:focus,
[data-theme="dark"] .form-group textarea:focus {
  border-color: #64b5f6;
}

[data-theme="dark"] .form-group button {
  background-color: #1565c0;
}

[data-theme="dark"] .form-group button:hover {
  background-color: #0d47a1;
}

[data-theme="dark"] #create-container aside {
  background-color: #2e2e2e;
  color: #ddd;
  border-right: 1px solid #444;
}

[data-theme="dark"] .form-group label {
  color: #eee;
}

[data-theme="dark"] #explanation-preview {
  background-color: #1e1e1e;
  color: #f5f5f5;
  border-left: 5px solid #ffca28;
}

```

